text: Henry K. Luning (January 24, 1905 – September 13, 1965) was an American competition swimmer who represented the United States as a 19-year-old at the 1924 Summer Olympics in Paris. Luning competed in the preliminary heats of the men's 100-meter backstroke in the Olympics, but failed to qualify for the event final. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1905 births Category:1965 deaths Category:American male backstroke swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of the United States Category:Sportspeople from Honolulu Category:Swimmers at the 1924 Summer Olympics
